`}}}}\"]\r\n\r\nEthiopia’s broad development goals are described in the Growth and Transformation Plan 2 (GTP2) (2015-2020), while agriculture sector goals are defined specifically in the National Agricultural Investment Framework (NAIF), which is currently being developed. The NAIF will operationalize the agricultural GTP 2, provide a framework for investment in the agriculture sector, and represent Ethiopia’s second generation Comprehensive Africa Agriculture Development Plan (CAADP) investment plan.\r\n\r\n[/kc_column_text][/kc_column_inner#][/kc_row_inner#][/kc_column_inner][kc_column_inner width=\"50%\" _id=\"560491\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{`479`:{`box`:{`padding|`:`inherit inherit inherit 15px`}}}}\"][vorosa_video_popup video_popup_random_key=\"57461\" source=\"youtube\" video_link=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6tfFRD0enV0\" video_box_bg=\"134\" _id=\"391260\" img_size=\"full\" video_box_icon=\"111\" icon_size=\"full\"][kc_single_image image_size=\"full\" _id=\"670153\" image_source=\"media_library\" image=\"1722\"][/kc_column_inner][/kc_row_inner][/kc_column][/kc_row]','Programs','','inherit','closed','closed','','1711-revision-v1','','','2018-06-05 21:53:40','2018-06-05 21:53:40','',1711,'http://www.moa-redfs.gov.et/1711-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1731,3,'2018-06-05 21:55:35','2018-06-05 21:55:35','[kc_row _id=\"848564\" cols_gap=\"{`kc-css`:{}}\" use_container=\"yes\" force=\"yes\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{`479`:{`box`:{`padding|`:`35px inherit 35px inherit`}},`767`:{`box`:{`padding|`:`30px inherit 30px inherit`}},`any`:{`background`:{`background|`:`eyJjb2xvciI6IiNmOGY4ZjgiLCJsaW5lYXJHcmFkaWVudCI6WyIiXSwiaW1hZ2UiOiJub25lIiwicG9zaXRpb24iOiIwJSAwJSIsInNpemUiOiJhdXRvIiwicmVwZWF0IjoicmVwZWF0IiwiYXR0YWNobWVudCI6InNjcm9sbCIsImFkdmFuY2VkIjowfQ==`},`box`:{`padding|`:`70px inherit 70px inherit`}}}}\"][kc_column width=\"12/12\" _id=\"40078\"][vorosa_section_title title=\"RmxhZ3NoaXAgUHJvZ3JhbXM=\" description=\"\" sec_title_box_icon=\"http://www.moa-redfs.gov.et/wp-content/plugins/vorosa-helper-plugin/include/shortcode/images/1.png\" _id=\"97879\" sec_title_icon_size=\"full\"][kc_row_inner _id=\"252528\" cols_gap=\"{`kc-css`:{}}\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{`479`:{`box`:{`margin|`:`30px inherit 30px inherit`}},`any`:{`box`:{`margin|`:`50px inherit 50px inherit`}}}}\"][kc_column_inner width=\"50%\" _id=\"331705\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{}}\"][kc_single_image image_size=\"full\" _id=\"730154\" image_source=\"media_library\" image=\"1716\"][/kc_column_inner][kc_column_inner width=\"50%\" _id=\"484781\"][kc_row_inner# _id=\"426855\" cols_gap=\"{`kc-css`:{}}\" row_class=\"video-info video-border\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{`479`:{`box`:{`padding|`:`inherit inherit inherit 0px`}},`767`:{`box`:{`padding|`:`inherit inherit inherit 0px`}},`999`:{`box`:{`padding|`:`inherit inherit inherit 0px`}},`any`:{`box`:{`padding|`:`35px inherit inherit 30px`}}}}\"][kc_column_inner# width=\"100%\" _id=\"959985\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{}}\"][kc_title text=\"QWdyaWN1bHR1cmUgR3Jvd3RoIFByb2dyYW0=\" _id=\"728930\" type=\"h3\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{`any`:{`title-style`:{`font-family|+.kc_title,.kc_title,.kc_title a.kc_title_link`:`Roboto Slab`,`font-size|+.kc_title,.kc_title,.kc_title a.kc_title_link`:`30px`}}}}\"][kc_column_text _id=\"113042\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{`any`:{`box`:{`padding|`:`inherit 27px inherit inherit`}}}}\"]<p>\r\nThe second phase Agriculture Growth Program (AGP 2), from 2015-2020, amounting to 581.8 million USD, is a multifaceted investment program operational in 157 high-potential woredas. The development objective of AGP 2 is to increase agricultural productivity and commercialization of smallholder farmers with particular focus on women and youth beneficiaries.</p>\r\n<p>The project comprises five components.</p>\r\n<p>1. Agricultural public support services will increase access to public agricultural services for smallholder farmers.</p>\r\n<p>2. Agricultural research will increase the supply of demand-driven agricultural technologies, which directly link to the other components.</p>\r\n<p>3. Small-scale irrigation will increase the access to and efficient utilization of irrigation water by smallholder farmers.</p>\r\n<p>4. Agricultural marketing and value chains will commercialize smallholder farmers through increased access to input and output markets.</p>\r\n<p>5. Project management, capacity building, and M&amp;E will ensure efficient project implementation, M&amp;E of results, and a consistent and effective approach to capacity building. Nutrition, gender, and climate smart agriculture considerations are mainstreamed throughout all components.</p>\r\n[/kc_column_text][/kc_column_inner#][/kc_row_inner#][/kc_column_inner][/kc_row_inner][kc_row_inner _id=\"382413\" cols_gap=\"{`kc-css`:{}}\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{`479`:{`box`:{`margin|`:`30px inherit 30px inherit`}},`any`:{`box`:{`margin|`:`50px inherit 50px inherit`}}}}\"][kc_column_inner width=\"50%\" _id=\"70672\"][kc_row_inner# _id=\"955625\" cols_gap=\"{`kc-css`:{}}\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{`479`:{`box`:{`padding|`:`inherit 0px inherit inherit`}},`767`:{`box`:{`padding|`:`inherit 0px inherit inherit`}},`999`:{`box`:{`padding|`:`inherit 0px inherit inherit`}},`any`:{`typography`:{`text-align|`:`right`},`box`:{`padding|`:`35px 30px inherit inherit`}}}}\" row_class=\"video-info video-border-two\"][kc_column_inner# width=\"100%\" _id=\"93408\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{`any`:{`box`:{`float|`:`right`}}}}\"][kc_title text=\"U3VzdGFpbmFibGUgTGFuZCBNYW5hZ2VtZW50IFByb2dyYW0NCg==\" _id=\"815464\" type=\"h3\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{`any`:{`title-style`:{`font-family|+.kc_title,.kc_title,.kc_title a.kc_title_link`:`Roboto Slab`,`font-size|+.kc_title,.kc_title,.kc_title a.kc_title_link`:`30px`}}}}\"][kc_column_text _id=\"378102\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{`any`:{`box`:{`padding|`:`inherit inherit inherit 27px`}}}}\"]<p>\r\nThe second phase Sustainable Land Management Program (SLMP 2), covering the years 2014-2019 and 107 million USD, conducts activities to rehabilitate and protect natural resources. Its objective is to reduce land degradation and improve land productivity in selected watersheds in the highlands of Ethiopia.</p>\r\n<p>There are four components to the project.</p>\r\n<p>1. Integrated watershed and landscape management supports scale-up and adoption of appropriate sustainable land and water management technologies and practices by smallholder farmers and communities.</p>\r\n<p>2. Institutional strengthening, capacity development and knowledge generation and management complements on-the-ground activities to be implemented under component one by strengthening and enhancing institutional capacity and building relevant skills and knowledge of stakeholders (including government agencies, research organizations and academia involved in the sustainable natural resource management, as well as the private sector, community leaders and smallholder farmers).</p>\r\n<p>3. Rural land administration enhances the tenure security of smallholder farmers in order to increase their motivation to adopt sustainable land and water management practices on communal and individual land.</p>\r\n<p>4. Enhancing the skills and capacities of project managers and administrators.</p>\r\n[/kc_column_text][/kc_column_inner#][/kc_row_inner#][/kc_column_inner][kc_column_inner width=\"50%\" _id=\"984589\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{`479`:{`box`:{`padding|`:`inherit inherit inherit 15px`}}}}\"][vorosa_video_popup video_popup_random_key=\"57461\" source=\"youtube\" video_link=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6tfFRD0enV0\" video_box_bg=\"134\" _id=\"151595\" img_size=\"full\" video_box_icon=\"111\" icon_size=\"full\"][kc_single_image image_size=\"full\" _id=\"907523\" image_source=\"media_library\" image=\"1718\"][/kc_column_inner][/kc_row_inner][kc_row_inner _id=\"673589\" cols_gap=\"{`kc-css`:{}}\" css_custom=\"{`kc-css`:{`479`:{`box`:{`margin|`:`30px inherit 30px inherit`}},`any`:{`box`:{`margin|`:`50px inherit 50px inh