 number of strategy papers including; a Mechanization Strategy; an Agricultural Extension Strategy and Nutrition Sensitive Agriculture Strategy. The sector also conducted a number of studies which among others include Contract Farming, seed and an Assessment of Extension Educational Materials.\r\n<h3>Livestock and Fisheries Production and Marketing Technical Committee (L&amp;FPM TC)</h3>\r\nThe L&amp;FPM TC has a unique structure in that it is chaired by two State Ministers, H.E Dr. Grebre Yohannes and HE W/ro Misrak. This TC has been Co-Chaired by FAO and UNDP since 2016/17. The TC has established four focused Task Forces; Mixed Crop and Livestock Production; Pastoral and Agro-Pastoral; Veterinary Services and Feed Quality and Fisheries and Aquaculture. On-going work under the various Task Forces include the production of Fisheries and Aquaculture Strategy, a Prosopis Management Strategy and a Pastoral Extension Strategy.\r\n<h3>Sustainable Land Management Technical Committee (SLM TC)</h3>\r\nIn 2016/2017 the SLM TC welcomed a new Chair State Minister Dr. Kaba Urgessa with World Bank and Germany GIZ continuing as Co-Chairs. The TC has five Task Forces including; Land Administration; Water Resources; Climate Change; Capacity Building and Best Practices. The sector produced a CRGE Mainstreaming Guideline and continue to work on a Capacity Development Strategy and a Lowland Natural Resource Management Assessment.\r\n<h3>Rural Job Opportunity Creation and Food Security Technical Committee (RJOC&amp;FS TC)</h3>\r\nIn 2016/2017 the RJOC&amp;FS TC also welcomed a new State Minister and TC Chair HE Ato Damenu Darota. The TC was Co-Chaired by USAID and World Bank. The TC has two Task Forces, namely Rural Job Opportunity Creation TF and the Food Security Task Force. The RJOC Directorate has just finalized the Rural Job Opportunity Creation Strategy.\r\n\r\n[/kc_column_text][/kc_column][/kc_row]','Platforms','','inherit','closed','closed','','130-revision-v1','','','2018-06-2