,'239-revision-v1','','','2018-06-27 16:17:44','2018-06-27 16:17:44','',239,'http://www.moa-redfs.gov.et/239-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1861,3,'2018-07-06 15:36:54','2018-07-06 15:36:54','[kc_row use_container=\"yes\" force=\"no\" column_align=\"middle\" video_mute=\"no\" _id=\"326632\"][kc_column width=\"12/12\" video_mute=\"no\" _id=\"375447\"][vorosa_section_title title=\"VGVjaG5pY2FsIENvbW1pdHRlZXM=\" description=\"__empty__\" sec_title_box_icon=\"http://www.moa-redfs.gov.et/wp-content/plugins/vorosa-helper-plugin/include/shortcode/images/1.png\" _id=\"482393\" sec_title_icon_size=\"full\"][/kc_column][/kc_row][kc_row use_container=\"yes\" force=\"__empty__\" _id=\"796319\" cols_gap=\"{`kc-css`:{}}\" container_class=\"video-info video-border\"][kc_column width=\"12/12\" video_mute=\"no\" _id=\"698739\"][kc_title text=\"QWdyaWN1bHR1cmFsIEdyb3d0aCBUZWNobmljYWwgQ29tbWl0dGVlIChBRyBUQyk=\" _id=\"901673\" type=\"h3\"][kc_column_text _id=\"59099\"]\n\nSince 2016/2017 the AG TC has been Chaired by new State Minister HE Tesfaye and Co-Chaired by Canadian Development and Italian Development. The TC consists of four Task Forces; Private Sector Development; Research and Technology; Extension and Capacity Building and Inputs and Finance. The sector produced a number of strategy papers including; a Mechanization Strategy; an Agricultural Extension Strategy and Nutrition Sensitive Agriculture Strategy. The sector also conducted a number of studies which among others include Contract Farming, seed and an Assessment of Extension Educational Materials.\n\n[/kc_column_text][kc_title text=\"TGl2ZXN0b2NrIGFuZCBGaXNoZXJpZXMgUHJvZHVjdGlvbiBhbmQgTWFya2V0aW5nIFRlY2huaWNhbCBDb21taXR0ZWUgKEwmRlBNIFRDKQ==\" _id=\"64994\" type=\"h3\"][kc_column_text _id=\"176145\"]\n\nThe L&amp;FPM TC has a unique structure in that it is chaired by two State Ministers, H.E Dr. Grebre Yohannes and HE W/ro Misrak. This TC has been Co-Chaired by FAO and UNDP since 2016/17. The TC has established four focused Task Forces; Mixed Crop and Livestock Production; Pastoral and Agro-Pastoral; Veterinary Services and Feed Quality and Fisheries and Aquaculture. On-going work under the various Task Forces include the production of Fisheries and Aquaculture Strategy, a Prosopis Management Strategy and a Pastoral Extension Strategy.\n\n[/kc_column_text][kc_title text=\"U3VzdGFpbmFibGUgTGFuZCBNYW5hZ2VtZW50IFRlY2huaWNhbCBDb21taXR0ZWUgKFNMTSBUQyk=\" _id=\"89443\" type=\"h3\"][kc_column_text _id=\"941432\"]\n\nIn 2016/2017 the SLM TC welcomed a new Chair State Minister Dr. Kaba Urgessa with World Bank and Germany GIZ continuing as Co-Chairs. The TC has five Task Forces including; Land Administration; Water Resources; Climate Change; Capacity Building and Best Practices. The sector produced a CRGE Mainstreaming Guideline and continue to work on a Capacity Development Strategy and a Lowland Natural Resource Management Assessment.\n\n[/kc_column_text][kc_title text=\"UnVyYWwgSm9iIE9wcG9ydHVuaXR5IENyZWF0aW9uIGFuZCBGb29kIFNlY3VyaXR5IFRlY2huaWNhbCBDb21taXR0ZWUgKFJKT0MmRlMgVEMp\" _id=\"951010\" type=\"h3\"][kc_column_text _id=\"438469\"]\n\nIn 2016/2017 the RJOC&amp;FS TC also welcomed a new State Minister and TC Chair HE Ato Damenu Darota. The TC was Co-Chaired by USAID and World Bank. The TC has two Task Forces, namely Rural Job Opportunity Creation TF and the Food Security Task Force. The RJOC Directorate has just finalized the Rural Job Opportunity Creation Strategy.\n\n[/kc_column_text][/kc_column][/kc_row]','Platforms','','inherit','closed','closed','','130-autosave-v1','','','2018-07-06 15:36:54','2018-07-06 15:36:54','',130,'http://www.moa-redfs.gov.et/130-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(1862,3,'2018-07-09 18:07:02','0000-00-00 00:00:00','[kc_row use_container=\"yes\" _id=\"712835\"][kc_column width=\"12/12\" video_mute=\"no\" _id=\"440738\"][kc_wp_widget data=\"\" _id=\"660784\"][/kc_column][/kc_row]','Test','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2018-07-09 18:07:02','2018-